On “Fox News Sunday” April 7, Mulvaney said: “Drug prices in this country actually came down last year for the first time in 50 years.
Drug prices are measured through a host of metrics and affected by all sorts of political and economic forces.
It could suggest that in the past year prescription drugs’ list prices have indeed dropped, and even by a meaningful amount.
But interpreting the data to mean that drug prices are down ignores crucial parts of the prescription drug marketplace.
